00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:04.700
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington DC.

00:00:23.270 --> 00:00:27.330 position:56%
&gt;&gt; John Cole: Well, good evening and
welcome to the Library of Congress.

00:00:27.330 --> 00:00:28.630
I'm John Cole.

00:00:28.630 --> 00:00:32.540
I'm the Director of Library of
Congress's Center for The Book.

00:00:32.540 --> 00:00:37.090
It's the book reading literacy
arm of the Library of Congress,

00:00:37.090 --> 00:00:40.860
which also takes a special interest
in promoting the history of books,

00:00:40.860 --> 00:00:44.290
reading, literacy, and libraries.

00:00:44.290 --> 00:00:48.100
We were created by Daniel
Boorstin, when he was the Librarian

00:00:48.100 --> 00:00:55.930 position:56%
of Congress in 1977, to reach out to
the general public, to promote books

00:00:55.930 --> 00:00:58.990
and reading in the name of
the Library of Congress.

00:00:58.990 --> 00:01:00.840
And so I'm very lucky.

00:01:00.840 --> 00:01:04.190
